HEADWORD: microcomputer
<hw>microcomputer</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>A small computer based on a
microprocessor; in practise, at any given time in the technology of
computer development, a <ex>microcomputer</ex> will be one that is less
powerful than a <contr>minicomputer</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> personal computer, PC.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

